    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-md-center">
            <div class="col-xl-6" style="color:white; text-align:center">
                <h4>Goals and xG</h4>
                xG is a metric which is calculated to reflect how many goals you might expect a player to
                score on average given the quality of opportunities to score that they had during a match.
                The line shows xG whereas the bars show the goals scored.
                <img src="/static/plots/xG_graph.png" class="img-fluid" alt="Responsive image">
            </div>
            <div class="col-xl-6" style="color:white; text-align:center">
                <h4>Assists and xA</h4>
                Similarly to xG, xA is a measure of an expected output you might expect on average from a player during a game,
                but this time for assists rather than goals. The line shows xA overlayed with the number of assists per game.
                <br><br><img src="/static/plots/xA_graph.png" class="img-fluid" alt="Responsive image">
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
